        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:19PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Antonito, or 26 miles northwest of Questa, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mesita, Jaroso, and Garcia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
